# Enforce LF line endings for all text files on every OS.
#
# Why this matters: the pack hashes every shipped file into
# MANIFEST.sha256 and ships POSIX .sh hook scripts. If a Windows clone
# with core.autocrlf=true rewrote LF -> CRLF on checkout, the sha256
# verification would fail ("supply-chain tampering") and the shell
# scripts would break. Pinning eol=lf keeps the working tree byte-identical
# across Windows, macOS, and Linux, so cross-platform integration stays
# deterministic.
* text=auto eol=lf

*.py     text eol=lf
*.sh     text eol=lf
*.json   text eol=lf
*.md     text eol=lf
*.mdc    text eol=lf
*.yml    text eol=lf
*.yaml   text eol=lf
*.txt    text eol=lf
*.sha256 text eol=lf
*.template text eol=lf

# Guard against accidental binary corruption (none ship today).
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.gz   binary
*.tar  binary
*.zip  binary
